# Access Token API

The Access Token API lets you perform actions on an individual [API Access Token](https://buildkite.com/docs/apis/rest-api#authentication), using the authentication details of REST API request.

<%= toc %>

## Get current API Access Token

Returns limited information about the current [API Access Token](/docs/apis/rest-api#authentication) being used to access the REST API.

```bash
curl "https://api.buildkite.com/v2/token"
```

```json
{
  "id": "b63254c0-3271-4a98-8270-7cfbd6c2f14e",
  "scopes": ["read_build"]
}
```

Required scope: none

Success response: `200 OK`

## Revoke current API Access Token

Revokes the API Access Token that was used to make the API request. Once revoked, the API Access Token can no longer be used.

```bash
curl -X DELETE "https://api.buildkite.com/v2/token"
```

Required scope: none

Success response: `204 No Content`
